n7\nReleased by WNU Features\nAdventurer Unlimited\nA\nMUCH appreciated friend\nmore than only an acquaint\nance\u2014of 30 years and more is Dr.\nFrank P. Thompson of Chicago.\nDr. Thompson's vocation is that\nof an eye specialist. In his profes\nsion he has an exceptionally large\npractice. For 18 months out of each\ntwo years he follows that vocation\nassiduously. The other six months\nof the two-year period he devotes\n\nto his avocation, his playtime, his\n\nhobby t 13 photogra P hm\nWild game in the African\nespecially elephants and ^ppopota\nmuses\nFRANK Thompson is a compara\ntively small man, under five feet\neight inches. I\nI should say. His\nweight. I wnidd\n^1 guess, is under 130\nP pounds. He has, I\nM imagine, celebrated\nnot fewer than 60\nI birthdays. He does\nI not look capable of\nwithstanding the\nrigors of life in the\nPATTERSON African wilds, but\nhe has done just\nthat on many a six-month stretch\nand seems none the worse for the\nher of native carriers accompany\nhim, enough to transport only the\nbarest necessities, including his\ncameras. His purpose is not the\nkilling ot. African game but to pho\ntograph it in its native habitat, es\npecially the elephant and the hippo\npotamus, on which he is ranked as\nan outstanding authority.\n\n\nWhile what he is loins,\u00ab\u00bb hi.\navocation involves constant danger.\nhis friends have learned to realize\nthat Frank can take care of him\nself. He always has come back,\nthough he has faced both charging\nelephants and hippopotamuses. On\noccasion he has shot the enraged I\nbeasta as f oic u e bctween his We\nand that of the charging animal,\nDuring World War II Frank sus-\npended his avocational trips into\nwild Africa. The war was being\nwaged in Africa as well as through\nout the remainder ol the world, and\nwiid men added to wild beast, rep\nresented more hazard than he cared\n!\u00efn h C nf b\n1 \u00abn\u00bbrim e n d lh\u00ee\nclub did not have ^n til Frank\nThompson completed \u00c2\u00cf\u00cf\u00ce\nwas at the Adventurers club that\nexperience.\nHe goes into Africa in the sim\nplest possible way. A small num\nGUIDES are a non-essential,\nfor Frank Thompson knows Af\nrica, and he knows African wild\nlife. He knows where to look\nfor those animals of which he\nwants pictures, and how to get\nto such places. Once he enters\nthe expanse of African Jungle,\nbush and forests his friends sel\ndom hear from him. He is out\nof the reach of postal services,\nof telegraph or radio sending\nstations.\nto encounter.\nON HIS photographic expeditions\nFrank has, on some occasions, un\ndertaken to secure specimens of\nsuch African animals as museums\nor other educational institutions\nmight need to complete a collection.\nHis one trophy, other than pictures.\nbe brought back from his re\ncentiy completed expedition, was\nthe long neck and head of a giraffe.\nIt now has joined the collection\nof trophies covering the walls of\nI have known Frank for the past\n30 years and more.\nFRANK does uot consider his\nexpeditions into Africa as ad\nventures. He thinks of them as\nbut a play time. Unless others\nwho know Africa and Us wild\ndenizens happen to meet across\nor around a club table, he does\nnot talk of them. When, under\nsuch conditions, he does talk It\nis in low tones, and in a mat\nter-of-fact way that displays no\nslightest element of boasting.\nI have heard him tell of charging\nelephants and hippopotamuses,\nwhen it was a case of his life or that\nof the enraged animal. Under such\nFrank will\ncannot afford to miss. Should it be\npossible to step aside and let the\nanimals pass, he does not attempt\nto stop them. To Frank Thompson\nsuch incidents were not adventures,\nthey were but ordinary incident\u00ab of\nbis picture-taking play time in Af\nrica.\n_ __\nFrank Thompson is one of the\nmost unusual characters I have\nknown and 14 ,s a Privilege to\nbe Permitted to call him\n''friend.\nproved a better political weather\nvane than the intricate mechanism\nused by Dr. Gallup,\n\nthemselves with the knowledge\nthere will be another chance in 1952\n\u2014only four years to wait\n\nPresident Truman's intuition\nThe Republicans can console\nNEW DELHI\ns\n4be something-for-nothing-sweets we\nwil1 continue to demand more and\nmore until there is nothing left but\nthe empty carton.\nHAVING had a generous taste ot\nNo Tickets Cost Rupees\n(/P)\nIndian\nrailway police recently arresed 600\npersons within four days for travel\ning without tickets a on the Delhl\nAmbala line. A total of 3,000 rupees\nwas collected in fines from those ar\ntesfed. Tickletless travelers are one\nof the Indian railroads' most acute\nproblems.","height":"27522","width":"21207"}}
